# AXA DevSecOps Reference: CODEOWNERS
#
# CODEOWNERS works with GitHub branch protection to require specific reviewers
# on PRs that touch specific paths. Combined with "Require review from Code
# Owners" branch protection rule, this enforces Security Champion approval
# on security-sensitive changes.
#
# AXA: SSDLC-IAM-01 (separation of duties), Git Branching Strategy

# Default owner: any change requires a Tech Lead review
*                               @your-org/tech-leads

# Security-sensitive files require a Security Champion in addition
/.github/workflows/             @your-org/tech-leads @your-org/security-champions
/.pre-commit-config.yaml        @your-org/security-champions
/.gitleaks.toml                 @your-org/security-champions
/Dockerfile                     @your-org/tech-leads @your-org/security-champions
/k8s/                           @your-org/tech-leads @your-org/security-champions
/terraform/                     @your-org/tech-leads @your-org/security-champions
/CODEOWNERS                     @your-org/security-champions
